      "body" : "@RajHassani Yes you can, see <a href=\"https://javadoc.io/doc/org.mockito/mockito-core/latest/org/mockito/Mockito.html#stubbing_consecutive_calls\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">here</a>."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 26747,
      "reputation" : 20445,
      "user_id" : 69875,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/595c6bb51e00b5dcb491c8648c0cc829?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Jonathan",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/69875/jonathan"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 97,
    "last_activity_date" : 1651589191,
    "last_edit_date" : 1651589191,
    "creation_date" : 1522858640,
    "answer_id" : 49655834,
    "question_id" : 40961057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Use Mockito's <a href=\"https://static.javadoc.io/org.mockito/mockito-junit-jupiter/4.5.1/org/mockito/junit/jupiter/MockitoExtension.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>MockitoExtension</code></a>. The extension is contained in a new artifact <code>mockito-junit-jupiter</code>:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n    &lt;groupId&gt;org.mockito&lt;/groupId&gt;\n    &lt;artifactId&gt;mockito-junit-jupiter&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n    &lt;version&gt;4.5.1&lt;/version&gt;\n    &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>It allows you to write tests as you would have with JUnit 4:</p>\n<pre><code>import org.mockito.junit.jupiter.MockitoExtension;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ExtendWith;\nimport org.mockito.InjectMocks;\nimport org.mockito.Mock;\n\n@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)\nclass MyTest {\n\n    @Mock\n    private Foo foo;\n\n    @InjectMocks\n    private Bar bar; // constructor injection\n\n    ...\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11726648,
      "reputation" : 26351,
      "user_id" : 8583692,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/joGZ9.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Mahozad",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8583692/mahozad"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1694754808,
    "creation_date" : 1694754808,
    "answer_id" : 77109761,
    "question_id" : 40961057,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For <strong>Kotlin</strong> and when annotating a field, make sure to mark it with <code>lateinit</code>:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-kotlin prettyprint-override\"><code>@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)\nclass MyTest {\n    @Mock\n    lateinit var list: List\n\n    @Test\n    fun `Test should work`() {\n        list.add(100)\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
